      <body>In my opinion it should be more &quot;secure&quot;:

@@@ruby
# This should be html_safe by default
&lt;%= I18n.t(:hello_user) %&gt;

# This should not be html_safe
&lt;%= I18n.t(:user_title, :username =&gt; @user.name) %&gt;
@@@

So basically if there is no interpolation it should be html_safe, if there is interpolation it should be escaped (because we all know 1 user with name &lt;script&gt;alert('I hax0red you')&lt;/script&gt; right)</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;In my opinion it should be more &quot;secure&quot;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;@@@ruby&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;This should be html_safe by default&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;%= I18n.t(:hello_user) %&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;This should not be html_safe&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;%= I18n.t(:user_title, :username =&amp;gt; @user.name)
%&amp;gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
&lt;code&gt;
So basically if there is no interpolation it should be html_safe, if there is interpolation it should be escaped (because we all know 1 user with name &amp;lt;script&amp;gt;alert('I hax0red you')&amp;lt;/script&amp;gt; right)&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
